other_tests.findings: The appendix is hyperemic and dilated up to 13 mm in diameter. There is small bowel tethered to the inflamed appendix with adjacent fat stranding and small amount of free fluid. No discrete abscess is seen though early phlegmonous changes difficult to exclude. No free air is present. The liver demonstrates homogenous attenuation throughout with no evidence of other focal lesions. The pancreas has normal attenuation throughout, without evidence of focal lesions. The spleen shows normal size and attenuation throughout. The kidneys are of normal and symmetric size with normal nephrogram.
